#   https://www.unicode.org/Public/17.0.0/ucd/UnicodeData.txt
#   https://www.unicode.org/Public/17.0.0/ucd/CompositionExclusions.txt
# Unicode 17.0.0. Five tables (NFC + NFD + NFKC + NFKD at v5.8.60;
# compat decomp uses 2-table split (sorted IDX + variable DATA blob)
# to keep size at ~87 KB instead of fixed-width 445 KB):
#   CCC:           8 hex chars/rec (cp u24 + ccc u8). Sorted by cp.
#   canonical:    20 hex chars/rec (cp u24 + count u8 + cp1 u24 + cp2 u24).
#   composition:  18 hex chars/rec (cp1 u24 + cp2 u24 + composed u24).
#   compat IDX:   12 hex chars/rec (cp u24 + data_off u24). Sorted by cp.
#   compat DATA:  variable per record — count u8 (2 chars) + cp1..cp_count
#                  u24 (6 chars each). Max count = 18 (U+FDFA Arabic
#                  ligature). Histogram (UCD 17.0.0): 1=2685, 2=648,
#                  3=411, 4=67, 5=16, 6=3, 7=1, 8=1, 18=1. Single-string
#                  variable (~41 KB) — under the 64 KB length cap of the
#                  cycc string-token encoding (offset<<16 | length, length
#                  is u16); no piece splitting needed.
# All sorted tables consumed by binary search in normalize.cyr;
# composition is sorted by (cp1, cp2) — primary cp1 with secondary
# linear-scan for cp2 within the cp1 run. Compat lookup: binary search
# IDX by cp → data_off → DATA[data_off] count + count cps.
# Public surface lives in normalize.cyr; this file is data.

